## What Was Done

### 1. Device Discovery & Serial Tooling
- Auto-detected Flipper on COM4, WiFi devboard on COM12
- Built 3 Python tools: [serial_commander.py](file:///E:/Thales/Thon/tools/flipper-zero/scripts/serial_commander.py), [scan_launcher.py](file:///E:/Thales/Thon/tools/flipper-zero/scripts/scan_launcher.py), [device_snapshot.py](file:///E:/Thales/Thon/tools/flipper-zero/scripts/device_snapshot.py)
- Captured full device snapshot (JSON) with corrected FW 1.4.3 CLI parsing

### 2. WiFi Marauder Companion App
- Built `esp32_wifi_marauder.fap` from source using `ufbt` (Target 7, API 87.1)
- Deployed to Flipper at `/ext/apps/GPIO/esp32_wifi_marauder.fap` via `ufbt launch`

### 3. Marauder Firmware Flash (ESP32-S2)
- **Previous firmware:** Blackmagic Debug Probe (factory default)
- **New firmware:** ESP32 Marauder **v1.11.0** (released 2026-03-10)
- **Method:** Web flasher at [esp.huhn.me](https://esp.huhn.me) via Chrome WebSerial
- **Files flashed:**

| Address | File | Size |
|---------|------|------|
| `0x1000` | `bootloader.bin` | 13 KB |
| `0x8000` | `partitions.bin` | 3 KB |
| `0xE000` | `boot_app.bin` | 8 KB |
| `0x10000` | `esp32_marauder_v1_11_0_flipper.bin` | 1 MB |

- Flash completed in **13 seconds**

## Issues Encountered
| Issue | Resolution |
|-------|-----------|
| Flipper stuck in DFU mode | User power-cycled and updated FW via qFlipper |
| COM4 locked by devboard GPIO | Deployed .fap via `ufbt launch` after closing qFlipper |
| ESP Flasher `ufbt build` missing submodule | Switched to web flasher (esp.huhn.me) — cleaner path |
| Bootloader.bin download was 404 HTML | Extracted correct binaries from FZ_Marauder_v2.8.zip bundle |

